-- Cyprus Popular Bank to Close 65 Branches and Cut Pay, CyBC Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-08-07T10:47:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/cyprus-popular-bank-to-close-65-branches-and-cut-pay-cybc-says.html
Cyprus Popular Bank pcl  plans to
close 65 branches in Cyprus and  Greece  by the end of the year,
to reduce operating expenses and boost profit,  Cyprus
Broadcasting Corp.  reported, without citing anyone.  The total branch network will be reduced to 225 and staff
pay and benefits will be cut, the state broadcaster said on its
website today. In Greece, pay cuts will mainly affect higher-
paid executives and the lender expects a large number of
resignations, CyBC said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  